2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the properties of different wireline channels, including power line channels, coaxial cables, and phone lines, which are all relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking): The paper proposes a statistical wireline channel model, which is a topic closely related to communication and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the variability of link topologies and wiring practices, which are relevant to systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper mentions the performance of equalization schemes, which is a topic relevant to multimedia.
